            . I live with Mr. William Geary - he <rs id="t18260216-67-viclabel344" type="occupation">keeps a cheesemonger's-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260216-67-victim584 t18260216-67-viclabel344"></join>, in Broad-street, Bloomsbury. I saw the prisoner come into the shop on the 17th of January, about half-past nine o'clock at night; he took a bladder of lard from off a pile of cheese, about two yards within the door, and ran out with it; I pursued him, and saw the officer bringing him back, and another man had the lard.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260216-67-person586">
                  WILLIAM 
                  REED
               <interp inst="t18260216-67-person586" type="surname" value="REED"></interp>
